// Threads

// In Zx there are no `async` or `await` keywords. Instead, you can use the `thread` keyword to create a new thread of execution.
// The `thread` module provides a way to create and manage threads in Zx.

// use the module
use thread;

fn doPrint() {
     println("Hello from thread!");
}

thread.spawn(doPrint); // spawn a new thread to run the doPrint function

thread.sleep(1000); // sleep for 1 second to allow the thread to finish